The Company and the Role:
Lehigh Hanson is one of the largest construction materials companies in North America with more than 550 active operations in the U.S. and Canada. Our core activities include the production and distribution of cement and aggregates, the two essential raw materials in concrete. Lehigh Hanson companies also produce ready-mixed concrete, asphalt and other concrete products.

Lehigh Hanson is part of the HeidelbergCement Group, a global leader in aggregates, cement, concrete, and other downstream activities. The Group employs over 60,000 people at more than 3,000 locations in 60 countries.

Calaveras Materials, part of Lehigh Hanson is seeking a qualified Accounting Associate. This position is located in Fresno, CA and will be responsible for the Financial Month End processes, AP invoices and Procurement-RMIM for functions for Aggregates, HMA and Ready Mix Concrete operations. Self-motivation, fast paced environment, prioritizing work to meet deadlines, and the ability to quickly resolve vendor concerns are essential.
This opportunity is perfect for the aspiring accounting specialist with a manufacturing/industrial background looking to grow their career with an industry leader. While focusing on providing top notch services to the plant, you will experience the opportunity to work alongside a tenured and knowledgeable team that will lead to the expansion of your knowledge base. This is a unique opportunity for you to begin your career with a proven leader in the heavy construction materials industry.

This position is located in Fresno, CA

Equal Opportunity Employer – Minority / Female / Veteran / Disabled

What you’ll get to do:
Accounts Payable function for aggregates, asphalt and ready mix operations;
Process vendor invoices and purchase orders on a daily basis;
Input data entry into JDE-Raw Materials Inventory Management system and reconcile on a monthly basis;
Maintaining fuel inventory and data entry in JDE system and reconcile on a monthly basis;
Prepare monthly accruals and check for validity;
Meeting Month-End closedeadlines, good attendance is crucial;
Communicate with Shared Service Center (SSC) on a routine basis;
Back up functions for and general office functions;
Responsible for performing special projects as assigned by the Accounting Supervisor;

Who we are looking for:
Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Business Administration or Finance, or Associate degree or equivalent industry experience;
Minimum of 1-3 years of experience in a manufacturing/office environment as well as APfunctions;
Basic Accounting knowledge and Accounting systems, i.e. JDE is required.
Proficient in Microsoft Office applications;
Effective oral and written communication skills.
Benefits & Compensation:

We appreciate that candidates have many questions when considering opportunities, so we want to let you know that we offer a comprehensive compensation and benefits package, which we like to share with candidates a little bit later in the process.

No search firms please.

